You can measure-- internet
pornography is extremely

00:29:40.000 --> 00:29:42.260 align:middle line:84%
similar to heroin--
one of the most

00:29:42.260 --> 00:29:43.590 align:middle line:90%
addictive things in the world.

00:29:43.590 --> 00:29:45.970 align:middle line:84%
And when you get addicted
to internet pornography,

00:29:45.970 --> 00:29:49.390 align:middle line:84%
your ability to feel passion
in a regular relationship

00:29:49.390 --> 00:29:50.600 align:middle line:90%
is diminished.

00:29:50.600 --> 00:29:52.640 align:middle line:84%
The same concept
is when you become

00:29:52.640 --> 00:29:56.450 align:middle line:84%
addicted to playing video games,
that's producing more dopamine.

00:29:56.450 --> 00:29:59.280 align:middle line:84%
Now dopamine is what
motivates us in life.

00:29:59.280 --> 00:30:00.990 align:middle line:84%
We feel motivated
towards things that

00:30:00.990 --> 00:30:04.080 align:middle line:84%
will make dopamine because
dopamine gives us pleasure.

00:30:04.080 --> 00:30:06.240 align:middle line:90%
Dopamine gives us focus.

00:30:06.240 --> 00:30:09.250 align:middle line:84%
Dopamine is always there when
something's interesting to us.

00:30:09.250 --> 00:30:13.700 align:middle line:84%
So anything that raises higher
dopamine levels-- that's

00:30:13.700 --> 00:30:17.710 align:middle line:84%
called overstimulation-- causes
are brain to change instantly.

00:30:17.710 --> 00:30:21.680 align:middle line:84%
Within a minute, the
receptor sites on the neurons

00:30:21.680 --> 00:30:23.910 align:middle line:90%
begin to close and disappear.

00:30:23.910 --> 00:30:25.420 align:middle line:90%
So maybe you had 100.

00:30:25.420 --> 00:30:26.810 align:middle line:90%
Now you have 70.

00:30:26.810 --> 00:30:29.730 align:middle line:84%
If you took cocaine, the
first shot of cocaine,

00:30:29.730 --> 00:30:33.250 align:middle line:84%
you've just lost 30%
of your receptor sites.

00:30:33.250 --> 00:30:33.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Forever?

00:30:33.990 --> 00:30:35.364 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: That's
the next question.

00:30:35.364 --> 00:30:37.780 align:middle line:84%
No, they will come back, as
long as you stop the cocaine.

00:30:37.780 --> 00:30:40.500 align:middle line:84%
And for some people,
like alcoholics,

00:30:40.500 --> 00:30:44.330 align:middle line:84%
they have a certain gene that
converts alcohol into dopamine.

00:30:44.330 --> 00:30:46.470 align:middle line:84%
Half the population could
never be an alcoholic.

00:30:46.470 --> 00:30:48.970 align:middle line:84%
They don't even drink because
they don't have that gene that

00:30:48.970 --> 00:30:51.110 align:middle line:90%
converts alcohol into dopamine.

00:30:51.110 --> 00:30:53.960 align:middle line:84%
But when those people who have
the gene, when they drink,

00:30:53.960 --> 00:30:55.560 align:middle line:90%
the dopamine levels shoot up.

00:30:55.560 --> 00:30:57.380 align:middle line:84%
The neurons start
down-regulating.

00:30:57.380 --> 00:30:59.070 align:middle line:90%
That's called down-regulation.

00:30:59.070 --> 00:31:02.955 align:middle line:84%
So now, normal life is no longer
giving you the stimulation

00:31:02.955 --> 00:31:03.830 align:middle line:90%
