00:53:06.089 --> 00:53:09.760 align:middle line:84%
is heart disease wasn't
even common until 1925.

00:53:09.760 --> 00:53:12.050 align:middle line:84%
This is a completely
modern invention.

00:53:12.050 --> 00:53:12.570 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't.

00:53:12.570 --> 00:53:13.390 align:middle line:90%
And going into the 1800s--

00:53:13.390 --> 00:53:13.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Heart disease.

00:53:13.840 --> 00:53:16.490 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Heart disease-- living
of a heart attack or arterial

00:53:16.490 --> 00:53:17.076 align:middle line:90%
plaque.

00:53:17.076 --> 00:53:18.200 align:middle line:90%
Where does that come from--

00:53:18.200 --> 00:53:18.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Where?

00:53:18.680 --> 00:53:19.510 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: --arterial plaque?

00:53:19.510 --> 00:53:21.050 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's a
whole other subject

00:53:21.050 --> 00:53:22.049 align:middle line:90%
that's not in this book.

00:53:22.049 --> 00:53:24.160 align:middle line:90%
But chlorine started that one.

00:53:24.160 --> 00:53:27.260 align:middle line:84%
Chlorine is, again, it's
a free-radical generator.

00:53:27.260 --> 00:53:28.860 align:middle line:84%
That's why chlorine
kills bacteria.

00:53:28.860 --> 00:53:31.380 align:middle line:84%
It's pure free radicals
putting into your body.

00:53:31.380 --> 00:53:34.070 align:middle line:84%
So we saved ourselves
from viral infections.

00:53:34.070 --> 00:53:35.570 align:middle line:84%
But now we're
drinking the chlorine.

00:53:35.570 --> 00:53:39.867 align:middle line:84%
The chlorine goes in the system
and attacks our arteries.

00:53:39.867 --> 00:53:41.700 align:middle line:84%
And then your body
builds plaque up in order

00:53:41.700 --> 00:53:43.801 align:middle line:90%
to protect the arteries.

00:53:43.801 --> 00:53:46.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Can we go back really
quickly to the happiness

00:53:46.050 --> 00:53:48.360 align:middle line:84%
factor-- the dopamine and
those types of things,

00:53:48.360 --> 00:53:51.950 align:middle line:84%
the SSRIs-- relationships--
people want to be happy.

00:53:51.950 --> 00:53:54.660 align:middle line:84%
If you're more happy, you're
more resilient to little things

00:53:54.660 --> 00:53:55.160 align:middle line:90%
that--

00:53:55.160 --> 00:53:55.740 align:middle line:90%
>>GRAY: Absolutely.

00:53:55.740 --> 00:53:57.970 align:middle line:84%
When your immune system
is working, all is magic.

00:53:57.970 --> 00:54:01.070 align:middle line:84%
And so when you're stressed,
depressed, anxious, not

00:54:01.070 --> 00:54:04.822 align:middle line:84%
motivated, not moving your body,
basically, your stress levels

00:54:04.822 --> 00:54:07.280 align:middle line:84%
are going to get higher and
higher until you have no stress

00:54:07.280 --> 00:54:07.950 align:middle line:90%
levels.

00:54:07.950 --> 00:54:09.200 align:middle line:90%
That's called adrenal burnout.

00:54:09.200 --> 00:54:11.366 align:middle line:84%
And then you're experiencing
the decline of old age.

00:54:11.366 --> 00:54:12.180 align:middle line:90%
You have no energy.

00:54:12.180 --> 00:54:12.971 align:middle line:90%
You have tiredness.

00:54:12.971 --> 00:54:14.260 align:middle line:90%
You won't have high cortisol.

00:54:14.260 --> 00:54:15.490 align:middle line:90%
You have no cortisol.

00:54:15.490 --> 00:54:17.482 align:middle line:84%
But you don't have
any DHEA, which

00:54:17.482 --> 00:54:19.190 align:middle line:84%
makes your estrogen
and your progesterone

00:54:19.190 --> 00:54:20.590 align:middle line:90%
and your testosterone.

00:54:20.590 --> 00:54:22.280 align:middle line:84%
So we see the average
50-year-old man

00:54:22.280 --> 00:54:24.550 align:middle line:84%
has half the testosterone
he had as a young man.

00:54:24.550 --> 00:54:26.430 align:middle line:84%
I have more than I
had as a young man.

00:54:26.430 --> 00:54:26.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:54:26.930 --> 00:54:29.116 align:middle line:84%
>>GRAY: Indigenous men
grow in testosterone

00:54:29.116 --> 00:54:31.240 align:middle line:84%
their lives-- not that much
higher, but the same as

00:54:31.240 --> 00:54:32.180 align:middle line:90%
when they're young.

00:54:32.180 --> 00:54:33.570 align:middle line:90%
This is a normal thing.

00:54:33.570 --> 00:54:35.010 align:middle line:84%
But today, it's
decline like that.

00:54:35.010 --> 00:54:38.180 align:middle line:84%
Libido goes down, and what does
that do for a relationship?

00:54:38.180 --> 00:54:39.030 align:middle line:90%
Huge problems.

00:54:39.030 --> 00:54:41.010 align:middle line:84%
And for women, they
start going menopause.

00:54:41.010 --> 00:54:42.510 align:middle line:84%
What they're getting
is an imbalance

00:54:42.510 --> 00:54:45.860 align:middle line:84%
